cardano/transaction/OutputReference.title: OutputReference
cardano/transaction/OutputReference.description:
An `OutputReference` is a unique reference to an output on-chain. The `output_index`
 corresponds to the position in the output list of the transaction (identified by its id)
 that produced that output

cred/Badge.title: Badge
cred/Badge.description:
A badge is a credential description, presented in the redeemer.

 Badges must match the different scope owner credentials.
 For example, when the owner is a ScriptCred,
 the presented credential must be a ScriptWithdrawal.

 Unique tokens can be presented as credentials.
 In such cases, we must check that the payment cred of the address
 owning the token is actually exercised:
  - either by a key in the required signatures
  - or by a script withdrawal

cred/ScopeOwnerCred.title: ScopeOwnerCred
cred/ScopeOwnerCred.description:
Credential of one scope owner.

 Using a unique token as credential is the most versatile approach,
 as it allows for more flexibility in managing ownership,
 and prevents the need to change the treasury address when
 transferring ownership of one scope.

cred/TokenProof.title: TokenProof
cred/TokenProof.description: Token policy ID and location in the transaction reference inputs

treasury/BudgetConfig.title: BudgetConfig
treasury/BudgetConfig.description:
Budget configuration for each token.
 For example, the config for Ada, or for USDM.

 For each token, the budget config specifies the rolling net limit amount and duration.
 It also keeps track of recent withdrawals to enforce the rolling net limit.

treasury/Scope.title: Scope
treasury/Scope.description: One scope of the multi-tenant treasury

treasury/ScopeAuth.title: ScopeAuth
treasury/ScopeAuth.description:
Authentication data for a scope UTxO.
 This can either be for a scope UTxO being spent or referenced.
 When the new output is "None", we consider the input

fields.title: badge
fields.description: Badge specifying how to check the scope owner's credentials.

fields.title: scope_input_index
fields.description: Index of the input (spent or ref) for the scope UTxO

treasury/Withdrawal.title: Withdrawal
treasury/Withdrawal.description:
One withdrawal from the treasury.
 It contains the amount withdrawn and when it happened (within a range).

anyOf.title: StartRecover
anyOf.description: Start recovering funds with a contestation period.

fields.title: presented_badges
fields.description:
List of badges presented in the redeemer.
 The list may contain variants granting the same permissions,
 so their count is not sufficient to check for all owners credentials.

fields.title: root_ref_index
fields.description: Index of the ref input containing the treasury root NFT.

fields.title: spent_input_index
fields.description: Index of the input being spent.

fields.title: next_output_index
fields.description: Index of the next output to be created.

fields.title: root_ref_index
fields.description: Index of the ref input containing the treasury root NFT.
